title: To Kill a Mockingbird
description: Set in the 1930s in Alabama, this novel explores themes of racial injustice and moral growth through the eyes of Scout Finch, a young girl witnessing her father's defense of a black man falsely accused of rape.
author: Harper Lee

title: Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone
description: Harry Potter, an eleven-year-old orphan, discovers that he is a wizard and is invited to study at Hogwarts. Even as he escapes a dreary life and enters a world of magic, he finds trouble awaiting him.
author: J.K Rowling

title: The Great Gatsby
description: A classic novel depicting the Jazz Age in America, exploring themes of wealth, love, and the American Dream through the eyes of narrator Nick Carraway and the mysterious Jay Gatsby.
author: F. Scott Fitzgerald

title: Pride and Prejudice
description: Jane Austen's classic novel delves into the lives of the Bennett family, particularly focusing on the spirited Elizabeth Bennett and her evolving relationship with the enigmatic Mr. Darcy.
author: Jane Austen

title: The Catcher in the Rye
description: A coming-of-age novel following the experiences of Holden Caulfield, a disenchanted teenager navigating the complexities of adolescence, identity, and societal expectations.
author: J.D. Salinger

title: The Alchemist
description: Paulo Coelho's allegorical novel follows Santiago, a shepherd boy on a quest for treasure, as he embarks on a journey of self-discovery, encountering spiritual lessons and profound insights.
author: Paulo Coelho

title: The Little Prince
description: Antoine de Saint-Exupéry's timeless tale of a young prince who travels from planet to planet, meeting quirky characters and learning valuable life lessons about love, friendship, and human nature.
author: Antoine de Saint-Exupéry

title: On Computable Numbers, with an Application to the Entscheidungsproblem
author: Alan Turing

title: Bitcoin: A Peer-to-Peer Electronic Cash System
author: Satoshi Nakamoto

title: The Da Vinci Code
description: A mystery thriller novel following symbologist Robert Langdon as he investigates a murder at the Louvre Museum, uncovering ancient secrets and hidden truths.
author: Dan Brown

title: The Hunger Games
description: Suzanne Collins' dystopian novel follows Katniss Everdeen as she navigates a brutal reality TV competition, confronting political intrigue, survival challenges, and questions of morality.
author: Suzanne Collins

title: The Road
description: Cormac McCarthy's post-apocalyptic novel follows a father and son as they journey through a bleak landscape, facing survival challenges and exploring themes of hope, despair, and human resilience.
author: Cormac McCarthy
